problem_text:
(G. Wilkes). A pro-p group is said to be accessible if there is a number
n = n(G) such that any finite proper reduced graph of pro-p groups with finite edge
groups having fundamental group isomorphic to G has at most n edges (J. Algebra,
525 (2019), 1–18).
Is every finitely presented pro-p group accessible?
P. Zalesskii
